cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image-to-image translation using deep learning techniques, specifically focusing on color transfer problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces a novel technique called network augmentation, which involves differentiable construction of intensity histograms from images. This technique falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses loss functions based on cyclic Earth Mover's Distance (EMD) and Mutual Information (MI), which are commonly used in information theory and signal processing, respectively. Therefore, the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper presents promising results for different datasets, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
